ories\n|\nNo matter how weird we all are, were still human.\n\n- Mekiah\n|\nOnce in a golden hour I cast to earth a seed. Up there came a flower, The people said, a weed.\n\n- Alfred Tennyson, The Complete Works of Alfred Tennyson\n|\nTo win the people, always cook them some savoury that pleases them.\n\n- Aristophanes, The Knights\n|\nWhen choosing your relationships, be guided by your life’s purpose, your vision and your dreams.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nYour life, your health and your weight are 80% due to what you eat, and 20% due to activity level, sunlight exposure, stress levels and adequate rest.\n\n- Nancy S. Mure, EAT! Empower, Adjust, Triumph!: Lose Ridiculous Weight, Succeed On Any Diet Plan, Bust Through Any Plateau in 3 Empowering Steps!\n|\nMeditation is the energy of the mind,\n\n- Lailah\n|\nI only care for the subjective life; I am very German, you see: The woods interest me, and the world does not.\n\n- Ouida, Wanda, Countess von Szalras.\n|\nI do not believe anyone can be perfectly well, who has a brain and a heart\n\n- Henry\n|\nthere isn't enough of anythingas long as we live. But at intervalsa sweetness appears and, given a chanceprevails.\n\n- Raymond Carver, Ultramarine: Poems\n|\nAll this he saw, for one moment breathless and intense, vivid on the morning sky; and still, as he looked, he lived; and still, as he lived, he wondered.\n\n- Kenneth Grahame, The Wind in the Willows\n|\nLike we all sync our watches every year, at the start and at the end of daylight saving time, we also need to sync our relationships once in a while.\n\n- Uday Mukerji, Love, Life, and Logic\n|\nAnd so that means...''We have to rob the Henley,' Simon said.Kat sank onto a truly uncomfortable sofa. 'Again.\n\n- Ally Carter, Perfect Scoundrels\n|\nThe more open we are, the more we can learn. The more we learn, the more we recognize that every one of us is a hero\n\n- Kim Ha Campbell, Inner Peace Outer Abundance\n|\nThe ability to differentiate between life challenges and who you are at the core is everything. A failed business, relationship or dream doesn’t make you a failure as a person.\n\n- Kim Ha Campbell, Inner Peace Outer Abundance\n|\nWhen you arise in the morning, think of what a precious privilege it is to be alive—to breathe, to think, to enjoy, to love—then make that day count!\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Life, the Truth, and Being Free\n|\nWhat ever you say or do, are reflections of what is in your heart.\n\n- Shawn\n|\nYou can’t be “it” for everyone. In fact, if you try to please everyone, you will please no one, especially yourself.\n\n- Amber Hurdle, The Bombshell Business Woman: How to Become a Bold, Brave, and Successful Female Entrepreneur\n|\nWhen I read books, it is like I have met the sacred souls.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nChristianity is a sacred path to pursue the Knowledge of Son of God, Jesus Christ.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nIf you were stranded in the ocean in a small boat with a paddle, I’d tell you to pray to God, but row for the shore!\n\n- Amber Hurdle, The Bombshell Business Woman: How to Become a Bold, Brave, and Successful Female Entrepreneur\n|\nFuture strong individuals will not take on personal sacrifices, hardships and corporate crap that sidetrack them from their dreams and goals.\n\n- Bill Jensen, Future Strong\n|\nI never knew the wonders of nature, until I began to walk with nature.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nIf we surrenderedto earth's intelligencewe could rise up rooted, like trees.\n\n- Rainer Maria Rilke, Rilke's Book of Hours: Love Poems to God\n|\nThere is nothing God loves more that keeping promises, answering prayers, performing miracles, and fulfilling dreams.\n\n- Mark Batterson, The Circle Maker: Praying Circles Around Your Biggest Dreams and Greatest Fears\n|\nWhenever He answers prayers, God usually prioritizes those by people who, instead of their mouths, have prayed with their hands and/or feet.\n\n- Mokokoma\n|\nThe nature of the world is 